plugins.name: comodo exporter
plugins.description:
This plugin helps you rename and export layers named $IMG in your Figma project based on special tags. You can choose between two workflows:

  1. Destructive export: Layers are renamed and export settings applied (JPG, PNG, SVG, @1x, @2x, @3x). Once renamed, the original $IMG layers are lost, and the plugin cannot be rerun unless you revert to an earlier version.
  2. Non-destructive export: The plugin creates a new page where it duplicates and renames all matching layers, preserving the original ones. You can delete the new page and restart anytime.

A Figma template will soon be provided with pre-set tags and an organized layout to make your workflow faster and more reliable. More detailed documentation will also follow.
plugins.tagline: Rename & export $IMG layers via tags. Template & docs coming soon for easy setup.

plugins.name: Import to Phase
plugins.description:
Transform your Figma designs into interactive, production-ready prototypes with Phase

• Create animations and interactions that actually ship to production

• Export as React components - no more design-to-code translation issues (Beta Release)

• Enable multiple simultaneous interactions (impossible in Figma alone)

• Work seamlessly between Figma and Phase with automatically organized interactions

• Professional animation tools: keyframes, motion paths, easing curves, and animation presets

• Real-time collaboration with developers and stakeholders


Join thousands of designers who bridge the gap between design and development! 🚀


Getting started is incredibly simple:

1 Select your design - Choose frames, components, or groups to export

2 Click Import - Phase allows you to choose to turn your variants into interactions

3 Open in Phase - Your designs are ready with interactions converted to Actions

4 Enhance & Export - Add animations and export as code or media files


Check our documentation for detailed guides and tutorials.


Documentation

• Quick Start Guide

• Interactions

• Video Tutorials


Features

🎯 Design to Code, Seamlessly

Unlike other prototyping tools, Phase exports your animations and interactions as production-ready React components. What you design is what gets built.

⚡ Multiple Simultaneous Interactions

Break free from Figma's limitations. Run multiple animations and interactions at the same time - just like in real applications.

🎨 Professional Animation Control

• Keyframes - Precise control over every animation property

• Path Animations - Motion paths for curved movements, trim paths for draw-on effects, and path morphing for shape transformations

• Animation Presets - ready-to-use animation effects (fade, scale, spin, trim, and more)

• Advanced Easing - Bezier curves, elastic, bounce, and custom easing


🔄 Import your Figma Interactions

You can choose to convert your Interactive components from Figma to Phase Actions.

🚀 Export Options That Matter

• React Components - Production-ready code

• Lottie - Lightweight animations for web and mobile

• Video/GIF - For presentations and social media

• dotLottie - Compressed animations with smaller file sizes


👥 Built for Teams

• Real-time collaboration with multi-cursor support

• Version history and commenting

• Share prototypes with stakeholders instantly


What makes Phase different?

From Design to Development

While other tools stop at visual prototypes, Phase generates actual code. Your beautiful interactions become real features, not just demos.

True Interactivity

Create conditional logic, decision-based flows, and complex user journeys. Phase combines visual design with programming logic.

Developer-Friendly

No more "lost in translation" between design and development. Developers receive clean, organized React components they can actually use.


Current Limitations

We believe in transparency. Here's what to expect:

• Borders become centered in Phase

• Text underlines and emojis aren't supported yet

• Blur/shadow effects may appear differently

• Polygons convert to paths

• Code export doesn’t support booleans and some animations yet because translating the canvas into code is really hard.. we’re working on it and shipping fast!


These limitations are temporary as we continuously improve the plugin.


FAQ

Can I use Phase without coding knowledge?

  1. Absolutely! Phase is designed for designers. The code export is a bonus for developer handoff, but you never need to write code yourself.

What happens to my Figma interactions?

  1. They're automatically converted to Phase Actions, ready for enhancement with advanced animations.

Can I collaborate with my team?

  1. Yes! Phase supports real-time collaboration, commenting, and version history. Share via restricted links, remix links, or prototype-only links.

What export formats are supported?

• Code: React components with CSS & JavaScript (Beta Release)

• Animation: GIF, MP4, Lottie (.json), dotLottie (.lottie)

• All exports maintain your animation timing and interactions

Is it free to try?

  1. Yes! Phase is free to use.


We're here to help you succeed:

📧 Email: support@phase.com

💬 Community: Join our community: https://community.phase.com/c/questions/


⠀

Ready to ship real interactions? Install Import to Phase and bridge the gap between design and development today! ✨
plugins.tagline: Design in Figma, Prototype in Phase

plugins.name: BlendAI
plugins.description:
BlendAI seamlessly integrates with Figma to let you generate high-quality images from text prompts or combine up to three reference images in a single click. It’s perfect for product mockups, hero banners, packshots, concept art, backgrounds, or quick visual inspiration—without ever leaving your Figma file.


Key Features:

• Simple prompt → image

Type a natural-language description and instantly receive a crisp, AI-rendered result.

• Multi-reference blending

Upload up to three reference images (for example: a product shot, a texture, and a background) and instruct BlendAI to place, style, or combine them.

Example: “Place @IMG_1 in front of @IMG_2 with the lighting mood of @IMG_3.”

• Six aspect-ratio presets

1:1 (Square), 16:9 (Landscape), 9:16 (Portrait), 4:3 (Classic), 3:4 (Portrait), 21:9 (Ultrawide)

• Instant one-click generation

No manual exports or workarounds—everything happens directly in Figma’s interface.

• Credit-based system

Includes a free 10-image starter pack. Easily top up credits from the “Get More” menu.

• History & quick re-use

View, revisit, and re-generate past images directly within the plugin.


BlendAI was built for designers who need on-the-fly visuals—whether it’s a quick hero image for a mockup, a polished packshot for a product page, or a fully blended scene combining multiple photo references. Try it free, then unlock larger credit packs for heavy usage.
plugins.tagline: AI image generation & multi-reference blending inside Figma for hero banners, mockups or backgrounds

plugins.name: Markdown Import
plugins.description:
このプラグインは、Google Docsやメモ帳などからコピーしたマークダウン形式のテキストを、Figmaのページ内にインポートするツールです。

「# 見出し1 」「 ## 見出し2」「### 見出し3」「本文」の構造を自動で判別し、それぞれに対応するコンポーネントを選択して挿入することができます。


【主な機能】

  1. マークダウン記法でコピー＆ペースト → 自動でレイアウト生成
  2. 見出し1〜3、本文、それぞれに同一ページ内の任意のコンポーネントを割り当て可能
  3. コンポーネント内のテキストレイヤーを自動で認識し、文字を置換


---


This plugin lets you import markdown-style text into your Figma page directly from Google Docs, Notepad, or any markdown editor.


It automatically parses the structure of your content—such as # Heading 1, ## Heading 2, ### Heading 3, and body text —and allows you to assign custom components for each section during import.


【Key Features】

  1. Paste markdown-formatted text and auto-generate layout in Figma
  2. Assign your preferred components for headings (H1–H3) and body text
  3. Detect and replace text inside the designated layer of each component
plugins.tagline: マークダウンのテキストをコンポーネントを適用してインポート | Import markdown into Figma with component mapping.

Sometimes Figma variables aren’t coming from inside the house. While this plugin has a likely very tiny amount of potential users, if I can help anybody save any time trying to locate and replace variables that are orphans or “remote”, then this has been worth it.


For whatever reason, variables in Figma can be attached to other libraries, older files, archived files even. This can cause major headaches when editing local variables and components don’t seem to respond to the edits.


I fully expect this plugin to have a limited lifespan as Figma themselves will likely improve variable handling during copy/pastes, schema renaming or other scenarios where variables can be orphaned.


In the meantime, I got you.
plugins.tagline: Replace those pesky remote variables!

135284.release_notes:

Also updated the data security details to let users know the network access is only for static items.

plugins.name: Blueprint
plugins.description:
Blueprint is a UX documentation tool that helps create UX flows & development instructions lightning fast. Just import your Figma designs to Blueprint and create UX flows on its grid-based canvas.

Visit blueprintapp.design to learn more about Blueprint!


Key features:

  1. Import Figma design: Import selected frames or the entire page.
  2. Grid canvas: Arrange and organize Figma frames super fast.
  3. UX flowchart: Draw UX flows with arrows and diagrams using Figma designs, making it easier to communicate with your teammates.
  4. Add annotations: Write down instructions or detailed guidance about a selected scene for clearer communications.


To get started:

  1. Install the Plugin from the Figma Community
  2. Enter your Figma File URL
  3. Choose specific Frames or import all Frames to Blueprint
  4. Click the "Open on Blueprint" button to begin designing your UX flows
plugins.tagline: High-fidelity UX Flows Made Effortless

Visualiza los cambios en tiempo real, guarda un historial detallado de tus ediciones y personaliza el diseño con colores que se ajustan a tu estilo. 129666.release_notes:
Release Note: Versión 1.1

Nuevas funcionalidades:
1.Soporte de idioma (Español/Inglés):
•Se ha implementado un selector de idioma en la UI del plugin, que permite cambiar entre español e inglés con un switch/slider intuitivo.
•El idioma de la interfaz (títulos, botones y textos) cambia dinámicamente según la selección del usuario.
•El texto de los logs registrados también cambia de idioma, mostrando la información correctamente tanto en español como en inglés, dependiendo del idioma seleccionado.
2.Actualización de sticker:
•Mejora de la gestión de stickers: Ahora, si un sticker ya existe, se actualiza con los nuevos logs en lugar de crear uno nuevo cada vez que se registra una edición.
•Si el sticker ya está presente, su contenido se limpia y se reemplaza con los nuevos logs, garantizando que no haya stickers duplicados.

Mejoras adicionales:
•Se mejoró el posicionamiento dinámico del sticker, asegurando que se mantenga correctamente ubicado en la esquina superior izquierda de la sección.
•Se optimizó el código para hacer el plugin más eficiente y evitar la creación de stickers innecesarios.

Fixes:
•Se solucionó un problema en el que un nuevo sticker se creaba cada vez que se registraba un log, incluso si ya existía uno previamente.
129666.tagline: Transforma tu flujo de trabajo: registra, organiza y visualiza cambios de diseño veloz.

This tool helps streamline the organization of complex design files and improves your workflow efficiency.

plugins.name: Interflow Connect
plugins.description:
Transform your design-to-management workflow with Interflow Connect, the Figma plugin that brings your UI flows directly into the Interflow. Designed for product teams and designers who demand efficiency, Interflow Connect eliminates the tedious process of manual uploads, allowing you to focus on what truly matters—creating exceptional user interfaces.


Streamlined Workflow, Unmatched Efficiency


With Interflow Connect, transferring your designs from Figma to Interflow is as simple as a few clicks. Select your desired frames within Figma, assign or create the appropriate flow and section names, and upload your screens directly to the Interflow without ever leaving your design environment. This seamless integration ensures your UI flows are always up-to-date and easily accessible for audits and reviews, making collaboration across teams more efficient than ever.


Secure, Direct Integration


Security and simplicity are at the heart of Interflow Connect. By inputting and authenticating your personal API key—generated from your Interflow settings—the plugin securely identifies your account, organization, and product. This robust authentication process guarantees that your design data is transmitted safely and accurately, offering a streamlined connection between your creative process in Figma and your product management workflow in Interflow.


Empower Your Product Design and Management


Interflow Connect is more than just a plugin—it’s the bridge between your design interface and your management platform. Whether you’re refining your product’s UI, conducting detailed audits, or ensuring that every screen aligns with your design strategy, this plugin is engineered to supercharge your workflow. Enjoy a smoother onboarding process, reduce manual errors, and keep your design projects perfectly synchronized with your product roadmap.


Experience a new level of productivity and collaboration by integrating your design and management tools. With Interflow Connect, you’re not just uploading screens—you’re empowering your team to build better products, faster.
plugins.tagline: The bridge between your interfaces in figma and your interflow.

plugins.name: Radial & Angular Blur FX
plugins.description:
Radial & Spin Blur is a professional Figma plugin that lets you add cinematic zoom or spin blurs in seconds while keeping full creative control.


Radial Blur (Zoom). Simulates rushing toward/away from a point (motion graphics, depth focus).

Spin Blur (Angular). Rotates pixels around a center (energetic, surreal visuals).

Anaglyph 3D (optional). Adds subtle red/cyan offset (retro depth accents).


Key features

  1. Live Preview – Resizable preview area shows the effect before you commit.
  2. 5 × 5 Focal-Point Grid – Pick any corner, edge, or true center.
  3. Smooth Intensity Slider – From whisper-soft haze to dramatic streaks.
  4. Large-Image Support – Works on layers / frames up to 1000 px with smart scaling.
  5. No Clipping – Padding logic prevents cut-offs even at high values or off-center points.
  6. One-Click Apply – Happy with the look? Hit Apply and you’re done.
  7. Modern UI – Fast, accessible, dark-mode aware.
  8. Usage Analytics – Pseudonymous event data is sent to Amplitude to improve performance and roadmap decisions (no personal identifiers are collected).


Typical workflow

  1. Select a layer or frame (≤ 1000 px).
  2. Pick Radial (Zoom) or Spin (Angular).
  3. Set the center on the 5×5 grid and adjust intensity.
  4. Preview the result live.
  5. Apply the blur — undo-friendly and non-destructive.


Perfect for

UI/UX designers, illustrators, social-media creators, or anyone who wants studio-grade motion blurs inside Figma.


Built with TypeScript, Figma Plugin API, and Amplitude telemetry for anonymous usage insights.
plugins.tagline: Zoom- or spin-style blur with live preview, 5×5 focal grid, anaglyph toggle, and one-click apply.

plugins.name: Update Genres Usage
plugins.description:
The page must have at least one of the following section hierarchies with the following names and elements within them:


- info (section)
    - genre (section)
        - genre name (shape with text)   <----|
    - game (section)                      (connection)
        - game name (shape with text)    <----|



Genre name must be connected to shapes containing game names and only to them.




For example we have such structure:




"info" section _______________________________________
|
| "genre" section _________________________
| |                                       |
| |  "genre name 1"        "genre name 2" |
| |_________|_____________________|________
|           |-------------------> |
| "game" s._|____       "game" s._|_____
| |         v   |       |         v    |
| | "game name1"|       | "game name2" |
| |______________       |_______________
|
|_______________________________________________




After the update, it will look like this


"info" section _______________________________________
|
| "genre" section _________________________
| |                                       |
| |  "genre name 1"        "genre name 2" |
| |     (2/2)                   (1/2)     |
| |_________|_____________________|________
|           |-------------------> |
| "game" s._|____       "game" s._|_____
| |         v   |       |         v    |
| | "game name1"|       | "game name2" |
| |______________       |_______________
|
|_______________________________________________
